<br>
Reading comprehension : stop putting words in my mouth. Where did you read it would *never* get fixed ?<br>
<br>
&gt;People like being free, after all.<br>
<br>
People need to figure out what &quot;free&quot; means, meaning they need to accept to separate church from state, which their religion and culture in its current form will never permit. That is the stumbling block you seem to have problems with. To build a democracy you first need a sense of nationalism. That doesn't exist. There is no such thing as &quot;Iraqi&quot;, all you have is a collection of tribes (some of them nomads that sedentarised in the last 50 years only). And they are all at each others throat.<br>
<br>
&gt;The trick is going to be in getting it set up in the first place.<br>
<br>
This is no &quot;trick&quot; - you can't force a national identity where there is no ethnic common ground ! The soviets tried it - look at what happened in Jugoslavia. The minute the red army left, the place imploded and is now divided again along ethnic boundaries.<br>
<br>
<br>
&gt;With Turkey as a model,<br>
<br>
Yeah - Turkey is a model... riiiight. They follow in lockstep right behind NK in human rights abuse. Great role model. The Iraqi are gonna love them when they find out they took a couple of oil fields in the bargain too. Or did you miss that part of the deal ?<br>
<br>
&gt;that alone will strike a bigger blow against Islamic fundamentalist terrorism <br>
<br>
Excuse me while i guffaw. You think that all the terrorist wanna-be's are going to be sitting by and watching you trying to build your puppet toy democracy ?  Just look at Israel : not two days without bodies coming in plastic bags. Yeah... the Israeli feel really free with their democracy right now within their 30 feet walls and tanks patrolling the streets.<br>
<br>
&gt;We're going to have an enormous groundswell of support from the Iraqi people once we free them<br>
<br>
Uh huh - and there will be manna raining from the sky too !<br>
<br>
&gt;For the good of Iraq, the U.S., and the entire world.<br>
<br>
Thank you for this brilliant expose Cpt Picard. I am sure that thesurvivors rising from the rubble in Baghdad will roll out the red carpet after the &quot;shock and awe&quot; operation <br>
<br>
Get real !<br>
<br>
S.<br>
