<br>
In my opinion, morality is based on culture, religion, and circumstance. There are no moral absolutes.  If you look at the natural law of life among animals the strong prey on the weak, the strong steal eggs from their prey, animals kill and fight each other over mates, animals eat their young to survive, animals rape other animals against their will.<br>
<br>
In the natural order, there is no morality, there is only the natural process of life, the realities of predator and prey, and the struggle of survival.<br>
<br>
When you bring man into the equation...man created civilization, or rather a code of ethics that man should live by in order to further our survival as a species. Throughout time, we pass down these morals to our children based on our culture. In some cultures it used to be ok to burn witches. In Aztec culture, human sacrifice was ok too. In the Amazon, cannibalism of your enemy tribe was morally a-ok up until recently as well. <br>
<br>
There are no moral rules than what society and our culture dictates. Morality is constantly evolving with humanity. <p><p><center>
